        <section class="education-overview">
            <div class="program-description">
                <h2>About Our Education Program</h2>
                <p>Helping street children enroll in government schools is our flagship program. We provide admission assistance, monitor attendance, and interface between schools and families. By 2016, over 100 children successfully enrolled in school who otherwise would have remained begging on the streets.</p>
                
                <p>The emphasis is on reducing the dropout rate. Those children in school "are choosing not to beg any longer" - a transformation that lies at the heart of our mission to help kids transition "from streets to classrooms."</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="program-features">
                <h2>What We Provide</h2>
                <div class="features-grid">
                    <div class="feature-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-user-plus"></i>
                        <h3>School Admission Assistance</h3>
                        <p>Complete support for enrollment in government schools, including documentation and liaison with school authorities.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="feature-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i>
                        <h3>Attendance Monitoring</h3>
                        <p>Regular tracking of student attendance and progress to ensure consistent educational engagement.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="feature-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-tshirt"></i>
                        <h3>Educational Supplies</h3>
                        <p>Uniforms, books, stationery, and other essential materials needed for school attendance.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="feature-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-chalkboard-teacher"></i>
                        <h3>Remedial Classes</h3>
                        <p>Additional tuition support and volunteer-led classes to help children catch up academically.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="feature-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-home"></i>
                        <h3>Family Interface</h3>
                        <p>Working closely with families to ensure continued support for children's education at home.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="feature-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-building"></i>
                        <h3>School Liaison</h3>
                        <p>Regular communication with schools to ensure proper integration and address any challenges.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section class="program-impact">
            <h2>Our Impact</h2>
            <div class="impact-stats">
                <div class="stat-item">
