                    <div class="stat-label">Successfully Enrolled by 2016</div>
                    <p>Children who transitioned from begging to schooling</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section class="daily-program">
            <h2>Daily Educational Activities</h2>
            <div class="schedule-grid">
                <div class="schedule-item">
                    <h3>School Hours</h3>
                    <p>Children attend regular government schools during standard hours, fully integrated with other students.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="schedule-item">
                    <h3>Summer Programs</h3>
                    <p>During school holidays, children attend our center daily (10am to 7pm) for educational activities and supervised learning.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="schedule-item">
                    <h3>Evening Tuition</h3>
                    <p>Volunteer teachers and college students provide remedial classes and homework support after school hours.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="schedule-item">
                    <h3>Creative Learning</h3>
                    <p>Art, sports, and creative activities that supplement formal education and build confidence.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section class="success-stories">
            <h2>Success Stories</h2>
            <div class="stories-grid">
                <div class="story-item">
                    <h3>Breaking the Cycle</h3>
                    <p>Many of our alumni have progressed to higher grades, with dozens passing class 10 exams and several securing their first jobs in hospitals and retail.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="story-item">
                    <h3>Choosing Education</h3>
                    <p>Our biggest achievement is that all children helped into school are now "choosing not to beg any longer" - preferring education over street life.</p>
